mark gallogly  wikipedia mark gallogly from wikipedia the free encyclopedia jump to navigation search mark gallogly january   is a managing principal and was a founder of the new york city based private investment firm centerbridge partners he served as a senior managing director of the blackstone group from may  to september  he was a member of president barack obamas presidents economic recovery advisory board he also serves on the advisory council of the hamilton project an economic policy group at the brookings institution the columbia business school board of overseers and the board of directors of the dana corporation in january  it was reported that gallogly was considering running for mayor of new york city gallogy obtained an undergraduate degree from the university of notre dame and an mba from columbia business school in  referencesedit  mark t gallogly profile forbescom retrieved    tapper jake  more details on the presidents economic recovery advisory board abc news retrieved    azi paybarah january   polling mark gallogly hedgefund manager and obama economic adviser for mayor capital new york   lise strickler becomes bride the new york times september    mark gallogly presidents economic recovery advisory board v t e private equity and venture capital investors investment strategy buyout venture growth mezzanine secondaries history history of private equity and venture capital early history of private equity private equity in the s private equity in the s private equity in the s investor types private equity investors venture capitalists corporate raiders this biography of an american economist is a stub you can help wikipedia by expanding it v t e retrieved from httpsenwikipediaorgwindexphptitlemarkgalloglyoldid categories living peoplecolumbia business school alumniamerican investment bankersuniversity of notre dame alumniprivate equity and venture capital investorsobama administration personnelamerican economist stubsamerican economistshidden catego